cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on understanding generalization in deep learning, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization algorithms and their role in implicit regularization, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of these concepts to computer vision tasks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the complexity measures and invariances in neural networks, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
